Will Smith is an American actor, comedian, producer, rapper, and songwriter who was born in West Philadelphia in 1968. He found fame as the star of the popular 1990s sitcom The Fresh Prince of Bel-Air, and has enjoyed success in television and film with roles in movies like Bad Boys, Independence Day, and Men in Black. Smith has been nominated for several major awards and has sold millions of records as a rapper. He resides in Los Angeles with his wife Jada Pinkett Smith and their two children.
